Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Fill and boil your #kettle{}.

Put a #large saucepan{} of water on to boil with @salt{1/2%tsp} for the pasta.

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once the oil is hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{260%g}. Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}, then cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @chicken stock paste{10%g}, @chopped tomatoes with onion and garlic{1/2}(finely chopped) and @boiled water for the sauce{75%ml} from your kettle to the chicken.

Stir in the @dried oregano{1%tsp}, bring to the boil, then reduce the heat to medium until the sauce is simmering.

Cook, stirring occasionally, until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked, ~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, add the @rigatoni pasta{180%g} to the pan of boiling water and bring back to the boil. Cook until tender, ~{12%minutes}.

When the pasta is cooked, drain in a #colander{} and return to the pan. Mix in the @creme fraiche{150%g} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Once the chicken is cooked, stir through the @peas{120%g}, then transfer to an #ovenproof dish{}.

Top with the creamy pasta and cover with the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g}.

Bake on the top shelf of your oven until the top is golden and a little crispy at the edges, ~{10-12%minutes}.

When ready, share your chicken pasta bake between your bowls.

Enjoy!